You are given the following reduction reactions and $E^{\circ}$ values:
$$
\begin{array}{ll}
\mathrm{Fe}^{3+}(a q)+\mathrm{e}^{-} \rightarrow \mathrm{Fe}^{2+}(a q) & E^{\circ}=+0.771 \mathrm{~V} \\
\mathrm{Fe}^{2+}(a q)+2 \mathrm{e}^{-} \rightarrow \mathrm{Fe}(s) & E^{\circ}=-0.447 \mathrm{~V}
\end{array}
$$
Calculate $E^{\circ}$ for the half-cell reaction $\mathrm{Fe}^{3+}(a q)+3 \mathrm{e}^{-} \rightarrow \mathrm{Fe}(s)$. Think step by step. Then, encode your final answer in <answer></answer>.
